0: Planned a quick local getaway from Baltimore
Nice hotel to stay for a Phily trip
Went for a birthday getaway and to eat a good Phily Chesesteak Maxs was Great
Rooms are OK and two queen bed option a bonus for families but good luck finding enough outlets for charging
Good for business trips not much else
We were part of a ATI Tour group and really found this hotel to be the best on the tour with it is location being close to restaurants
My family and I enjoyed our stay
All in all not a great experience for me and family next time I will avoid this hotel and staying in Westins which I had great experience in the past
I had stay here again on business or family travel
1: One of my colleagues stayed at this hotel on a business trip and I asked him that I would deliver there two items I bought online so he could bring them to me
The metal bed frame was too large for the mattress it sat on which resulted in me tripping twice on the bed frame
Additionally the bed frame was larger than the mattress which created a tripping hazards
Just stay in the hotel again during business trip in the area about same as experience I had last year
Our room carpeting was in such poor and loose condition we were tripping on it
The only suggestion I have to make it a perfect trip was for the hotel to offer a continental breakfast
I was not feeling the best during the end of the conference and when I realized there was no work reason to linger I decided to cut my trip short
After a long trip disappointing to have to deal with this
Although it served its purpose for our trip
Let me add that I was staying at this hotel under my relatives family discount so I did n’t want to complain but this was totally unacceptable
